  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "First make the pickle. Chop the cucumber in half lengthways\nand remove the seedy core, then thinly slice the cucumber and\nred onion and add them to a jar or deep bowl. Add the apple cider\nvinegar to a saucepan and bring to a simmer over a medium heat.\nAdd the salt and sugar, mixing well until they dissolve. Pour the\npickling mixture over the sliced cucumber and red onion and let\nthem sit for 30 mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Now for the tofu skewers. Roughly chop the tofu into 3cm (11⁄4in)\ncubes and add to a bowl."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Roughly chop the garlic, shallot and the white of your\nlemongrass (saving the green part for later) and add to a blender\nalong with the ground coriander, ground turmeric and chilli\npowder. Add a splash of water and blend until smooth. Add this\nmarinade to the bowl of tofu and mix thoroughly, then set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, make the satay sauce. Start by very finely chopping\nthe garlic and shallot. Get a saucepan over a medium heat, then add\nthe vegetable oil and your chopped shallot and garlic. Fry for a few\nminutes until the veg is golden."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add the chilli powder, ground turmeric and coriander to the\npan and mix well. Next, you’re going to want to go in with the\ntamarind paste, sugar, salt, peanut butter and the green parts of the\nlemongrass you chopped up earlier. Pour in 180ml of water\nalong with coconut milk and soy sauce. Bring to the boil, making\nsure to regularly stir it so the bottom of the pan doesn’t burn. This\nwill take about 5 mins. Turn the heat down and let it simmer for\n30 mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Preheat the grill to medium-high."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Thread 3 or 4 marinated tofu cubes onto each of your skewers\n(depending on size and personal preference)."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Get a griddle pan hot over a medium-high heat. Lightly brush\nyour tofu skewers with vegetable oil and add a few to the pan at a\ntime, making sure not to overcrowd them. Cook each batch for a\nfew minutes on each side until you get nice char lines."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Once they’ve got a nice bit of colour, pop your skewers under the\nhot grill for 10 mins to finish them off. Meanwhile, thinly slice\nthe red chilli, chop the coriander and crush the peanuts in a pestle\nand mortar."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Serve the tofu skewers with the satay sauce and pickled\ncucumber and red onion. Garnish with the sliced red chilli, chopped\ncoriander and crushed peanuts."
    }
  ],
